<title type="html"><![CDATA[9/16(Thu)China's season of regulatory crackdown/ Advantages and Disadvantages of Virtual Meetings(host:Joyce)]]></title>

<content type="html" xml:base="http://www.royalclub.tw/bbs3/viewtopic.php?t=541&amp;p=564#p564"><![CDATA[
Place: On-Line Zoom Meeting <br /><!-- m --><a class="postlink" href="https://zoomtw.zoom.us/j/92987266213?pw">https://zoomtw.zoom.us/j/92987266213?pw</a><!-- m --> ... 09#success<br />會議 ID: 929 8726 6213<br />密碼: 112233 <br />Agenda:<br />07:00-7:05 pm Opening Remarks <br />07:05-7:40 pm Session 1 Group Discussion<br />07:40-8:00 pm Presentation (At least two members of each table are invited, 2 mins / each member)<br />8:00-8:05 pm Break<br />8:05-8:40 pm Session 2 discussion<br />8:40-9:00 pm Presentation<br /><br />Session I:<br />From tech to education, China's season of regulatory crackdown<br /><!-- m --><a class="postlink" href="https://economictimes.indiatimes.com/news/international/world-news/from-tech-to-education-chinas-season-of-regulatory-crackdown/articleshow/85766231.cms">https://economictimes.indiatimes.com/ne ... 766231.cms</a><!-- m --><br /><br />1.Do you think that China’s education crackdown will be beneficial to reduce the financial burdens of parenting and help boost the country’s declining birth rate?<br />2.China regulates children under the age of 18 will only be allowed to play online games between 8 p.m. and 9 p.m. on weekends and national holidays, with a maximum playtime of three hours each week. Do you think it will be able to stop growing addiction to what it describes as &quot;spiritual opium&quot;?<br />3.China cracked down on what it described as a &quot;chaotic&quot; celebrity fan culture, barring platforms from publishing popularity lists and regulating the sale of fan merchandise. What’s your opinion about celebrity fan culture in Taiwan? <br />4.Some younger Chinese are embracing ‘lying flat’. They don’t buy property; don’t buy a car; don’t get married; don’t have children; and don’t consume. Does this life attitude poses a social and economic threat?<br />5.Why does China want to weaken the influence of outspoken tech tycoons like Jack Ma?<br />Session II:<br />Advantages and Disadvantages of Virtual Meetings<br /><!-- m --><a class="postlink" href="https://www.displaynote.com/blog/advantages-and-disadvantages-of-virtual-meetings">https://www.displaynote.com/blog/advant ... l-meetings</a><!-- m --><br /><br />1.What are the advantages and disadvantages of online meetings?<br />2.How to improve the quality of on-line meetings?<br />3.Do you prefer to join the English club meeting online or a traditional in-person face-to-face gathering.? Why?<br />4.What's the best way to make a meeting fun?<br />5.How to make your virtual meetings more interactive?<br />P.S.<br />1.參加三次後，只要繳交1,000元(學生500元)，即可成為ROYAL終身會員!<br />2.請帶著開放與熱情來參加自由的全英文會話聚會~<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://www.royalclub.tw/bbs3/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=89">AndrewWang</a> — Wed Sep 08, 2021 11:20 pm</p><hr />
]]></content>
